abstract: Dignitaries from across the globe gathered to remember the anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz.
snippet: Dignitaries from across the globe gathered to remember the anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia called for vigilance “not to miss when the first sprouts of hatred, of chauvinism, of xenophobia and anti-Semitism start to rear their ugly head.”

abstract: President Trump’s lawyer would not address whether his team would request changes to the schedule for Saturday.
snippet: President Trump’s lawyer would not address whether his team would request changes to the schedule for Saturday.
lead_paragraph: Jay Sekulow, the president’s lawyer and one of the leaders of his defense team, declared that “nothing has changed in the last day and a half of their two and a half days.”

headline_main: Trump Impeachment: Highlights From Thursday’s Senate Trial

abstract: Most were only vacant for a few minutes.
snippet: Most were only vacant for a few minutes.
lead_paragraph: The rules of the Senate trial say the senators are supposed to be sitting in their seats throughout the presentation. In President Trump’s trial, they are treating that rule rather liberally.
headline_main: Republicans and Democrats treat the rule to stay in their seats rather liberally.

abstract: At the anti-capitalist capitalist event, radical sentiments erupt in unexpected places.
snippet: At the anti-capitalist capitalist event, radical sentiments erupt in unexpected places.
lead_paragraph: Everyone at Davos this year really wants you to know that the corporate world is cleaning up its act. Yes, O.K., maybe they’ve said things like that before, but this year they mean it. Walking around, I thought at times that I had mistakenly wandered into a business-casual Bernie Sanders rally: unrestrained capitalism has gone too far; corporate greed has endangered the planet; the time has come for radical change. On the train into Davos, a representative of Philip Morris told me that the company was “dedicated to a smoke-free future.” I blinked; she said the company had “a duty” to millions of addicted smokers.

abstract: A senator creates an extensive drawing of the Capitol while he listens to the prosecution’s presentation.
snippet: A senator creates an extensive drawing of the Capitol while he listens to the prosecution’s presentation.
lead_paragraph: Senator Rand Paul of Kentucky had a white legal notepad in front of him as Thursday’s impeachment trial began — and he was busy doodling.
headline_main: Rand Paul takes a break from doodling to silently make a point.

abstract: The House speaker has closely managed President Trump’s impeachment from the beginning. She is not letting up during his Senate trial.
snippet: The House speaker has closely managed President Trump’s impeachment from the beginning. She is not letting up during his Senate trial.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s motorcade was winding through Jerusalem on Wednesday, en route to a state dinner hosted by the president of Israel, when she placed perhaps the most important call of her day — to Representative Adam B. Schiff, the man leading the charge to remove President Trump from office.

headline_main: Even From Half a World Away, Pelosi Keeps a Tight Grip on Impeachment
headline_print_headline: Pelosi Still Overseeing the Proceedings From 5,900 Miles Away

abstract: Representative Jerrold Nadler argued that the nation’s founders envisioned that impeachment would be required for presidential abuses of power.
snippet: Representative Jerrold Nadler argued that the nation’s founders envisioned that impeachment would be required for presidential abuses of power.
lead_paragraph: Representative Jerrold Nadler, Democrat of New York and chairman of the House Judiciary Committee, began the House presentation on Thursday with an hourlong lecture on the constitutional history of impeachment.
